HEADWORD: Pampered
<hw>Pam"pered</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Fed luxuriously;
indulged to the full; hence, luxuriant; <as>as, <ex>pampered</ex>
children</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pampered</xex> boughs.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Pampered</xex> insolence.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Pope.</au> -- <wordforms><wf>Pam"pered*ness</wf>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms> <rj><au>Bp. Hall.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

